# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional build-time GitHub token.
#
# Project data is fetched from the public GitHub REST API at BUILD time. The
# unauthenticated limit is 60 requests/hour per IP, which is plenty for local
# dev. In CI (or if you build frequently) set a token to raise the limit to
# 5000/hour. A classic token with NO scopes (or a fine-grained token with
# public read) is sufficient — we only read public repositories.
#
# 1. Copy this file to `.env`  (the real `.env` is gitignored)
# 2. Paste your token below
#
# If unset, the build still works: on any rate-limit/network failure it falls
# back to the committed src/data/projects.fallback.json snapshot.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
GITHUB_TOKEN=
